            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1680016330695-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the courgette has softened, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and cook for 1 min or until the liquid has evaporated</p><p>Once evaporated, add your <strong>single creamy soy</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 5-6 min, or until the sauce has thickened to a double cream-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1680016335096-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
